    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera represents the pinnacle of the 996.2 evolution, featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. Power is delivered through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing short, precise throws and a direct mechanical interface. The chassis architecture utilizes a MacPherson strut front and a sophisticated multi-link rear suspension, maintaining excellent kinematic geometry. This example has been proactively maintained, including an IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS) to ensure long-term reliability of the crankcase assembly. The braking system features four-piston monoblock calipers acting on cross-drilled, vented rotors for exceptional thermal management and pedal feel. A mechanically sound driver\u2019s car, it exhibits consistent compression and a dry undercarriage, making it an ideal candidate for the discerning Porsche purist.",
